1. Definitions

   1.1. "Software": Refers to all source code, binaries, files, documentation, and associated materials provided in this repository and subdirectories.
   1.2. "Non-Commercial Use": Refers to usage limited to the following purposes:
      1.2.1. Personal projects that do not generate revenue, directly or indirectly.
      1.2.2. Academic research, teaching, or learning.
      1.2.3. Non-revenue-generating open-source projects that do not receive any form of monetary support, including but not limited to sponsorships, donations, crowdfunding, or any other financial contributions.
   1.3. "Commercial Use": Refers to any use intended to generate revenue, either directly or indirectly, including but not limited to:
      1.3.1. Use by businesses, corporations, organizations, or commercial entities.
      1.3.2. Integration into products or services that are sold, licensed, or monetized.
      1.3.3. Use in business operations, internal tools, or proprietary systems.
      1.3.4. Revenue-generating activities involving advertising, sponsorships, or partnerships.
   1.4. "Team Use": Refers to any collaborative usage of the Software by more than one individual on a single project, whether commercial or non-commercial.
   1.5. "User": Refers to any individual, team, or entity accessing, downloading, modifying, or using the Software in any capacity.


